There is not enough color and she is already pretty fair toned so she blends into the backdrop of the elevator lobby. The second outfit is a black two piece…but the dancers are also wearing similar outfits and accessories so she blends in here as well. Winter and Soyeon stand out more with their hair colors, makeup, and outfits. Their outfits are more glamorous maybe because their stylists coordinated with the production crew to understand the MV set themes and worked around that instead? Overall love the song and MV direction but needed better coordination on the idol’s side.

It is assumed that they trained to sing and dance, that is supposed to be their vocation but now many and many use singing and dancing to climb the ranks to be models, influences and actors. All very bad, concentrate on being singers and dancers first, otherwise you would have been better off studying acting, modeling or fashion designer.
